    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Parents Will Be Revered by Children Fitted for Heaven</strong>&mdash;In the word of God we find a beautiful description of a happy home and the woman who presides over it: &ldquo;Her children arise up, and call her blessed; her husband also, and he praiseth her.&rdquo; What greater commendation can be desired by the mistress of a home than that which is here expressed?<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"HR 12-1-1877\" data-link=\"504.1277\">The Health Reformer, December, 1877</span>.</span></a></sup>",
