    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 534.5 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>The Joys of Heaven to Begin in the Home</strong>&mdash;Heaven and earth are no wider apart today than when shepherds listened to the angels&rsquo; song. Humanity is still as much the object of heaven&apos;s solicitude as when common men of common occupations met angels at noonday and talked with the heavenly messengers in the vineyards and the fields. To us in the common walks of life heaven may be very near. Angels from the courts above will attend the steps of those who come and go at God&apos;s command.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">9<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"DA 48.1\" data-link=\"130.138\">The Desire of Ages, 48</span>.</span></a></sup>",
