    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The service rendered in sincerity of heart has great recompense. &ldquo;Thy Father which seeth in secret Himself shall reward thee openly.&rdquo; By the life we live through the grace of Christ, the character is formed. The original loveliness begins to be restored to the soul. The attributes of the character of Christ are imparted, and the image of the Divine begins to shine forth. The faces of men and women who walk and work with God express the peace of heaven. They are surrounded with the atmosphere of heaven. For these souls the kingdom of God has begun. They have Christ&apos;s joy, the joy of being a blessing to humanity. They have the honor of being accepted for the Master&apos;s use; they are trusted to do His work in His name.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">11<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"DA 312.1\" data-link=\"130.1491\">The Desire of Ages, 312</span>.</span></a></sup>",
