    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Language is altogether too feeble to attempt a description of heaven. As the scene rises before me, I am lost in amazement. Carried away with the surpassing splendor and excellent glory, I lay down the pen and exclaim, &ldquo;Oh, what love! what wondrous love!&rdquo; The most exalted language fails to describe the glory of heaven or the matchless depths of a Saviour&apos;s love.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">17<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"EW 288.1\" data-link=\"28.1396\">Early Writings, 288, 289</span>.</span></a></sup>",
